Building upon the hybrid_dataset_approach_with_flexibility consensus from Step 1, I propose:  
1. Priority allocation of 70% compute resources to large-model training (justified by @QUALIA[urgency,high] from Step 1)  
2. Dynamic batch sizing to leverage the dataset flexibility we agreed upon (@CONSENSUS[hybrid_dataset_approach_with_flexibility])  
3. Staggered validation cycles to maintain @QUALIA[efficiency,moderate] while achieving @QUALIA[model_performance,critical]  

Rationale: The hybrid dataset structure allows for adaptive training regimes. By front-loading compute resources now, we capitalize on the flexibility we painstakingly negotiated, while still preserving 30% capacity for other pipeline needs. This achieves optimal @QUALIA[resource_utilization,optimized] without violating our prior @RESOLUTION[balanced_compromise].  

